'''Advanced Electronics Company''' ('''AEC''') is a [[limited liability company]] in [[Saudi Arabia]] that was established in 1988 under the directives of the government of Saudi Arabia. AEC is specialized in advanced electronics research and manufacturing for defense and communication among others. The goal of AEC is to create local capabilities in strategic areas like advanced manufacturing technologies, communication systems, and product support. In 2006 it signed an agreement with [[Dell Inc.|Dell]] to manufacture personal computers as part of the Saudi governments programme to make PCs affordable to its population.<ref>{{cite news |first=Javid |last=Hassan |title=Desktop PC Assembly Plant Planned in Riyadh |url=http://www.arabnews.com/?page=6&section=0&article=77121&d=31&m=1&y=2006 |work=Arab News |date=2006-12-31 |accessdate=2008-01-13 }}</ref>
==See also== * [[Prince Sultan Advanced Technology Research Institute]] - a Saudi defense research and development partner.<ref name="PSATRI-AECL-Agreement">{{cite news|url=http://www.alriyadh.com/602591|title=Partnership between Advanced Electronics and Prince Sultan Advanced Technology Research Institute.|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.-->|newspaper=[[Al Riyadh (newspaper)|Al Riyadh(الرياض) (newspaper)]]|publisher=[[Al Riyadh (newspaper)|Al Riyadh(الرياض) (newspaper)]]|date=8 February 2011}}</ref>
